<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pitch1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pitch,</orth> subst. a thick black substance obtained by boiling down tar: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.54" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 57</bibl>. Proverbially defiling: <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.455" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 455</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.196" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 196</bibl>. Emblem of moral pollution: <cit><quote>so will I turn her virtue into p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.366" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 366</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>